🔷 6. END-TO-END FLOWS

💾 Save (Update Name)

User edits name field
    ↓
Controller detects dirty state
    ↓
User clicks Save
    ↓
Controller → Transport (PATCH /api/builder/unit-of-measures/:id)
    ↓
Transport: auth + validation + expectedUpdatedAt check + mutation receipt
    ↓
Application.updateUnitOfMeasureUseCase(id, input) — orchestrates:
    ↓
  [1] Application asks Domain → normalize and validate input (pure, no DB needed)
    ↓
  [2] Application asks Data → nameExists check (fetch the fact Domain needs)
    ↓
  [3] Application asks Domain → assertNameAvailable(exists) (evaluate the rule)
    ↓
  [4] Application asks Data → updateRecord (execute the mutation)
    ↓
  [5] Application asks Data → getById (fetch authoritative snapshot)
    ↓
Application returns snapshot
    ↓
Transport returns { unitOfMeasure }
    ↓
Controller replaces state with snapshot
    ↓
dirty = false, UI updates

🗑️ Delete

User clicks Delete
    ↓
UI: confirmation dialog
    ↓
Controller → Transport (DELETE /api/builder/unit-of-measures/:id)
    ↓
Transport: auth + expectedUpdatedAt check + mutation receipt
    ↓
Application.deleteUnitOfMeasureUseCase(id) — orchestrates:
    ↓
  [1] Application asks Data → getDeleteState(id) (fetch the facts Domain needs)
         ↳ Data has no opinion on whether deletion is allowed — it only fetches
    ↓
  [2] Application asks Domain → assertUOMDeletable({ categoryLinks, serviceLinks })
         ↳ Domain is the authority — it evaluates the rule against the fetched facts
         ↳ Domain has no DB access — Application feeds it what it needs
    ↓
  ❌ Domain throws → Application propagates → Transport returns structured error
         ↓
      Controller surfaces error to UI
         ↓
      UI displays: "This unit of measure is linked and cannot be deleted"
    ↓
  ✅ Domain approves → Application asks Data → deleteRecord(id)
    ↓
Transport returns { ok: true }
    ↓
Controller navigates away or refreshes list

Note on ordering:
Data always fetches before Domain evaluates — not because Data outranks Domain,
but because Domain is pure. It cannot query the database. Application fetches
the facts first, then hands them to Domain for a decision. Domain still owns
the rule. Application owns the orchestration sequence.

