🔷 9. WHY UOM IS THE RIGHT STARTING POINT

UOM is the simplest fully-formed record view in the system:
* One FieldSection, one PrimaryRow, no ChildScopedRows
* One domain rule (delete blocked if linked)
* Full test coverage already exists (SIMPLE_TABLE_DOMAIN_STATUS: Done)
* No transactions required (single-row operations)
* No worker workflows

This makes it the ideal table to:
1. Establish the canonical packages/execution use case pattern
2. Establish the canonical packages/db repository pattern
3. Establish the canonical packages/domain rule pattern
4. Prove the refactor without risk to complex workflows
5. Create the template that work-orders, templates, and imports will follow

Every more complex table follows this exact same structure — with more sections, more domain rules, and more use cases on top.

